Condolences continue to pour in for the former Newcastle united Midfielder who collapsed and died during training with his club Beijing Enterprise on Monday. The Ivory Coast player joined Beijing Enterprises FC from Newcastle United in February this year after a 7-year career with Newcastle. Tiote was part of the Ivory Coast team that went to win the 2015 Africa Cup of Nations trophy. He played for his national team between 2010 and 2015 and had more than 50 caps.He went on to have a successful international career where was signed by Newcastle in 2010 for a reported 3.5m signing fee.The Confederation of African Football (CAF) extended their condolences&#8221;The reputation of African football, its notoriety, are made by players like him be it on the continent or outside. His death is a shock, especially when one considers the conditions. My thoughts are with his family, his teammates and with all the football family in C te d&#8217;Ivoire,&#8221; Ahmad Ahmad said Tiote&#8217;s former team Newcastle United extended condolences to their former player on twitter and reflected on a goal that he scored for them.We&#39;ll never forget you, Cheick. pic.twitter.com/c8aO6EyW5w&mdash; Newcastle United FC (@NUFC) June 5, 2017&nbsp;Chelsea FC also sent their condolences.Rest in peace, Cheick Tiot &#8211; our condolences are with his family and friends. pic.twitter.com/F6FvoNkna1&mdash; Chelsea FC (@ChelseaFC) June 5, 2017Meanwhile Vincent Kompany of Manchester City described Tiot as one of the toughest teammates he had ever played with.I am speechless and so incredibly sad. Cheick Tiot was one of the nicest and toughest teammates I have ever had. Rest in peace brother.&mdash; Vincent Kompany (@VincentKompany) June 5, 2017A great goal will live forever. Cheick Tiot sadly passed away in training today &#8211; RIP pic.twitter.com/Ltd20CPub0&mdash; The Soccer Life (@TheSCRLife) June 6, 2017 Our thoughts are with the family and friends of Cheick Tiot pic.twitter.com/PInDznDc7t&mdas